    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n    <title>Refactoring Demonstration</title>\n    <style>\n        body {\n            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\n            line-height: 1.6;\n            max-width: 800px;\n            margin: 0 auto;\n            padding: 20px;\n        }\n        .container {\n            display: flex;\n            flex-direction: column;\n            gap: 20px;\n        }\n        .code-block {\n            background-color: #f5f5f5;\n            padding: 15px;\n            border-radius: 5px;\n            font-family: monospace;\n            white-space: pre-wrap;\n        }\n        button {\n            padding: 8px 16px;\n            background-color: #4CAF50;\n            color: white;\n            border: none;\n            border-radius: 4px;\n            cursor: pointer;\n        }\n        button:hover {\n            background-color: #45a049;\n        }\n        .result {\n            margin-top: 10px;\n            padding: 10px;\n            border: 1px solid #ddd;\n            border-radius: 4px;\n        }\n    </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n    <h1>Refactoring Demonstration</h1>\n    <p>Refactoring is the process of restructuring existing code without changing its external behavior. Below is an example of refactoring a simple function.</p>\n    \n    <div class=\"container\">\n        <section>\n            <h2>Original Code</h2>\n            <div class=\"code-block\">\nfunction calculateTotal(items) {\n    let total = 0;\n    for (let i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {\n        if (items[i].price > 100) {\n            total += items[i].price * 0.9; // 10% discount for expensive items\n        } else {\n            total += items[i].price;\n        }\n    }\n    return total;\n}\n            </div>\n            <button onclick=\"runOriginal()\">Run Original</button>\n            <div id=\"originalResult\" class=\"result\"></div>\n        </section>\n\n        <section>\n            <h2>Refactored Code</h2>\n            <div class=\"code-block\">\nfunction calculateTotal(items) {\n    return items.reduce((total, item) => {\n        return total + (item.price > 100 ? item.price * 0.9 : item.price);\n    }, 0);\n}\n            </div>\n            <button onclick=\"runRefactored()\">Run Refactored</button>\n            <div id=\"refactoredResult\" class=\"result\"></div>\n        </section>\n    </div>\n\n    <h3>Refactoring Benefits:</h3>\n    <ul>\n        <li>More concise and expressive code</li>\n        <li>Uses modern JavaScript features (reduce)</li>\n        <li>Eliminates temporary variables</li>\n        <li>Easier to read and maintain</li>\n        <li>Same functionality with less code</li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <script>\n        const testItems = [\n            { name: \"Item 1\", price: 50 },\n            { name: \"Item 2\", price: 120 },\n            { name: \"Item 3\", price: 80 },\n            { name: \"Item 4\", price: 200 }\n        ];\n\n        // Original function\n        function calculateTotalOriginal(items) {\n            let total = 0;\n            for (let i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {\n                if (items[i].price > 100) {\n                    total += items[i].price * 0.9; // 10% discount for expensive items\n                } else {\n                    total += items[i].price;\n                }\n            }\n            return total;\n        }\n\n        // Refactored function\n        function calculateTotalRefactored(items) {\n            return items.reduce((total, item) => {\n                return total + (item.price > 100 ? item.price * 0.9 : item.price);\n            }, 0);\n        }\n\n        function runOriginal() {\n            const result = calculateTotalOriginal(testItems);\n            document.getElementById('originalResult').textContent = \n                `Total: $${result.toFixed(2)} (Original)`;\n        }\n\n        function runRefactored() {\n            const result = calculateTotalRefactored(testItems);\n            document.getElementById('refactoredResult').textContent = \n                `Total: $${result.toFixed(2)} (Refactored)`;\n        }\n    </script>\n</body>\n</html>"
